Abuja (Sundiata Post) â€“ Senator Ben Murray Bruce has directed Silverbird Group that all new vehicles purchased on behalf of the company will be electric vehicles. Senator Ben Bruce took to his Twitter handle to announce that his company, Silverbird Group, is set to go green by using electric cars. Bruce in his tweet also revealed that he has given a company-wide directive that all new vehicles purchased on behalf of the Silverbird Group will be electric vehicles. He tweeted; I have just given a company-wide directive that all new vehicles purchased on behalf of Silverbird Group will be electric vehicles. We are going to be the first company to go all green. Also, we will not issue any car-loan to any staff except they want to buy an electric car.  